<law><law_id>558</law_id><section_number>2-2015</section_number><catch_line>LICENSE; DUE DATE.</catch_line><history/><order_by>2-2015</order_by><metadata/><url>/2-2015/</url><token>2-2015</token><structure><unit label="division" level="1" identifier="II">Division II - Planning and Development</unit><unit label="part" level="3" identifier="2">PART 2 - FINANCE</unit><unit label="chapter" level="4" identifier="2">CHAPTER 2. - REVENUE AND TAXATION</unit><unit label="article" level="2" identifier="B">ARTICLE B. - PRIVILEGE LICENSE TAXES [1]</unit></structure><referred_to_by/><text><section id="1525" prefix="(a)"><text>Unless otherwise provided in the schedule of taxes provided for in &#xA7;2-2013, each privilege license issued shall cover the twelve-month period beginning June 1 of each calendar year and ending May 31 of the subsequent calendar year.</text><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(a)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(a)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(a)</prefix_anchor><level>1</level></section><section id="1526" prefix="(b)"><text>The privilege license tax is due on June 1 of each year. If, however, a person begins a business after June 1, the tax for that year must be paid before the business is begun.</text><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(b)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(b)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(b)</prefix_anchor><level>1</level></section><section id="1527" prefix="(c)"><text>The Revenue Collector shall not issue a license until the tax levied under &#xA7;2-2013 has been paid.</text><type>section</type><prefixes><section>(c)</section></prefixes><entire_prefix>(c)</entire_prefix><prefix_anchor>(c)</prefix_anchor><level>1</level></section></text></law>
